cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC

The paper deals with regular languages, automata on infinite words, and monadic second-order theories, which are all topics related to logic and formal languages. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses decidability, which is a topic related to algorithms and complexity, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions automata, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
